Utilizing FSL dtifit, a single diffusion tensor or ellipsoid was constructed at each voxel in the brain from the DWI scans that had undergone eddy and EPI correction. The eigenvalues of the diffusion tensor (λ1, λ2, λ3) were then used to generate scalar maps of anisotropy and diffusivity, indicating the lengths of the ellipsoid’s longest, middle, and shortest axes. Fractional anisotropy (FA) values were obtained from the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
